      "content": "While protecting local jobs sounds noble, the reality is that tariffs simply shift the cost of those jobs to consumers and foreign exporters, often leading to higher prices and reduced wages for everyone. Relying on tariffs to keep factories open is a short-term fix that ultimately weakens the American economy by making our goods less competitive globally, which hurts the very workers you're trying to help in the long run. True job security comes from investing in education, infrastructure, and fair wages, not from punishing our trading partners and inflating the cost of living.",
